File: Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize has announced that as of Saturday, the number of confirmed COVID-19 in South Africa is 3,034. JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 3,034. Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize says 108,021 tests have been conducted, mostly in the private sector. Mkhize says the number of death now stands at 52. Explainer: New amendments to the lockdown regulations Since Friday the number of new confirmed cases has gone up by 251. The minister confirmed the numbers on Saturday. For an updated number of cases, click here. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.